WEBVTT

00:02.370 --> 00:04.436
-<i> Previously on</i> The Strain.
-<i> Too long I've lived.</i>

00:04.438 --> 00:06.438
<i> Too much I've seen.</i>

00:06.440 --> 00:09.141
(screaming)
Strigoi!

00:09.143 --> 00:12.478
-<i> I've seen them in the tunnels.</i>
<i> It's turning people into</i>

00:12.480 --> 00:14.780
hungry vermin.
- They are

00:14.782 --> 00:17.549
<i> no longer people. And to think</i>
<i> they are is very dangerous.</i>

00:17.551 --> 00:20.486
- You do not have
the luxury of choice anymore.

00:20.488 --> 00:22.321
All we can do now is fight.

00:22.323 --> 00:25.057
- (man):<i> Is the war</i>
<i> already lost?</i>

00:25.059 --> 00:28.627
<i> Are we destined to be</i>
<i> cattle for monsters or now</i>

00:28.629 --> 00:30.896
<i> that the enemy has shown</i>
<i> his face, do we have</i>

00:30.898 --> 00:34.500
<i> a fighting chance?</i>
(creatures screaming)

00:34.502 --> 00:37.236
- I've kept my part
of the agreement;

00:37.238 --> 00:39.238
<i> the Master will keep his.</i>

00:39.240 --> 00:41.073
- Behold.

00:41.075 --> 00:43.475
- Ha! Ha! Ha! Ha!
- (boy): What about Mom, Dad?

00:43.477 --> 00:45.811
-<i> I don't know where your mom</i>
<i> is, but I'm gonna find her.</i>

00:45.813 --> 00:47.246
No!
- (boy): Mom!

00:47.248 --> 00:50.749
- It's not her anymore!
- (boy): No! Mom!

00:50.751 --> 00:51.984
-<i> The Master will use</i>
<i> your wife's love...</i>

00:51.986 --> 00:54.153
- Eph, don't.
<i> - ...for her son</i>

00:54.155 --> 00:58.323
to pursue us
to the ends of the Earth.

00:58.325 --> 01:01.260
- Let him try.
-<i> Despite all evidence</i>

01:01.262 --> 01:03.328
<i> to the contrary, you cling</i>

01:03.330 --> 01:05.864
to the delusion
that you will prevail?

01:05.866 --> 01:09.768
The great game is over, Jew.
- Not while I still breathe.

01:12.540 --> 01:14.606
(barking)

01:18.245 --> 01:22.514
- Abraham Setrakian,
come and have your soup.

01:22.516 --> 01:25.417
Abraham!

01:25.419 --> 01:28.520
- I'm not hungry.

01:30.391 --> 01:33.792
Tell me one more story,<i> Bubbeh.</i>
- It's late now, Abraham.

01:33.794 --> 01:37.362
There's barely enough
time for a tale. Maybe...

01:37.364 --> 01:40.966
while you finish your soup.

01:40.968 --> 01:43.235
What story do you want to hear?

01:43.237 --> 01:46.371
- Sardu,<i> Bubbeh.</i>
Will you tell me his story?

01:46.373 --> 01:49.074
- Sardu? Again?

01:49.076 --> 01:51.810
Even if it is a scary one?

01:53.380 --> 01:55.614
Very well, Abraham.

01:55.616 --> 01:59.318
But I want a clean plate
at the end of it all.

02:01.288 --> 02:04.256
There once was a great nobleman

02:04.258 --> 02:06.725
named Jusef Sardu.

02:06.727 --> 02:10.929
Since childhood,
he suffered from gigantism.

02:10.931 --> 02:12.998
His body was aged,

02:13.000 --> 02:15.901
his bones were bent
and riddled with aches,

02:15.903 --> 02:18.570
so he was forced
to walk with a cane.

02:20.508 --> 02:24.109
<i> His was a beautiful sword-cane</i>

02:24.111 --> 02:28.247
<i> with a white-gold handle</i>
<i> and a silver blade.</i>

02:28.249 --> 02:30.916
(in foreign language)

02:30.918 --> 02:32.584
(speaking foreign language)

02:32.586 --> 02:36.121
<i> His disease made him aware</i>

02:36.123 --> 02:38.023
<i> of the frailty of life.</i>

02:38.025 --> 02:41.293
<i> So as a result, he was</i>

02:41.295 --> 02:44.930
<i> very kind to others,</i>
<i> especially children.</i>

02:44.932 --> 02:48.200
(Sardu and children
speaking in foreign language)

02:48.202 --> 02:50.135
(Sardu laughing)

02:50.137 --> 02:52.004
(Sardu speaking
in foreign language)

02:52.006 --> 02:55.774
<i> However, Sardu's brother,</i>

02:55.776 --> 03:00.679
<i> the baron, was shamed</i>
<i> by his sibling's affliction.</i>

03:00.681 --> 03:03.615
<i> He organized a hunting trip</i>

03:03.617 --> 03:05.984
<i> with his brother</i>
<i> and his cousins,</i>

03:05.986 --> 03:10.322
<i> because he believed the blood</i>
<i> of the Great Grey Wolf</i>

03:10.324 --> 03:12.624
<i> could cure the disease</i>

03:12.626 --> 03:15.694
<i> afflicting Jusef.</i>
(dogs barking)

03:17.898 --> 03:20.566
<i> Day after day,</i>

03:20.568 --> 03:25.470
<i> they walked in search</i>
<i> of the Great Grey Wolf.</i>

03:25.472 --> 03:28.140
(men laughing and speaking
in foreign language)

03:33.147 --> 03:35.314
(strange croaking)

03:35.316 --> 03:38.183
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!

03:38.185 --> 03:40.185
(word in foreign language)

03:40.187 --> 03:44.489
- (Bubbeh):<i> But...</i>
<i> something other than a wolf</i>

03:44.491 --> 03:46.992
<i> was alive in the woods.</i>

03:46.994 --> 03:49.094
(man speaking foreign language)

03:49.096 --> 03:52.231
(creature croaking
and growling)

03:54.501 --> 03:56.768
(man speaking foreign language)

03:56.770 --> 03:59.938
- (Bubbeh):<i> And it started</i>
<i> hunting them.</i>

03:59.940 --> 04:03.875
<i> One by one, the members</i>

04:03.877 --> 04:06.011
<i> of the hunting party left...</i>

04:06.013 --> 04:08.046
(creature growling)

04:08.048 --> 04:14.353
<i> ...until Jusef found himself</i>
<i> completely alone.</i>

04:14.355 --> 04:17.789
(Sardu panting)

04:20.861 --> 04:23.695
<i> A certainty grew in his heart:</i>

04:23.697 --> 04:26.098
<i> his brethren were dead,</i>

04:26.100 --> 04:28.133
<i> and it was up to him</i>

04:28.135 --> 04:30.269
<i> to kill the beast</i>

04:30.271 --> 04:32.671
<i> or die trying.</i>

04:44.718 --> 04:48.453
Finish your soup, Abraham,
and I'll finish my tale.

04:53.727 --> 04:55.727
When he finally

04:55.729 --> 04:58.664
encountered the creature...

04:58.666 --> 05:01.933
it was not a wolf at all.

05:01.935 --> 05:04.469
(Sardu panting)

05:29.997 --> 05:32.297
(strange growling)

05:32.299 --> 05:33.999
(flesh tearing sound)

05:34.001 --> 05:37.669
<i> It was an ancient,</i>
<i> hungry being.</i>

05:39.640 --> 05:41.940
<i> And as it gazed</i>

05:41.942 --> 05:46.345
<i>at the giant's body, it smiled.</i>

05:49.283 --> 05:52.050
- Young hunter.

05:56.457 --> 05:58.623
So, you think

05:58.625 --> 06:01.059
you're going to kill me...

06:01.061 --> 06:03.628
with that?

06:03.630 --> 06:05.897
(growling)

06:08.802 --> 06:12.537
I can smell the silver
on the blade.

06:12.539 --> 06:15.874
(laughing)

06:15.876 --> 06:21.146
Do you think you are faster

06:21.148 --> 06:23.582
than me?

06:32.659 --> 06:35.827
(coughing)

06:35.829 --> 06:39.264
(Sardu groaning)
- This body:

06:39.266 --> 06:41.266
frail, brittle.

06:41.268 --> 06:43.769
My will, my soul...

06:43.771 --> 06:46.938
(Sardu groaning)

06:46.940 --> 06:50.242
...I pass unto you.

06:52.279 --> 06:54.846
- Ah!

06:54.848 --> 06:57.516
(Sardu coughing)

07:00.020 --> 07:01.753
- As a blessing,

07:01.755 --> 07:04.856
I bestow them.

07:04.858 --> 07:07.325
(Sardu groaning)

07:20.908 --> 07:23.008
(Sardu growling)

07:26.380 --> 07:29.681
(Sardu screaming)

07:34.054 --> 07:36.455
(panting)

07:47.935 --> 07:51.470
(soft growling)

07:58.412 --> 08:01.780
- (Bubbeh):<i> Sardu returned</i>
<i> to his village weeks later,</i>

08:01.782 --> 08:04.249
<i> but was never again seen</i>

08:04.251 --> 08:07.452
<i> outside his castle walls.</i>

08:07.454 --> 08:10.455
<i> Not in daylight, that is.</i>

08:10.457 --> 08:13.792
<i> Some say he was much changed.</i>

08:13.794 --> 08:17.496
(weird croaking)

08:19.433 --> 08:21.266
<i> And soon,</i>

08:21.268 --> 08:24.769
<i> young children began</i>
<i> disappearing from the village,</i>

08:24.771 --> 08:27.839
<i> vanishing from their beds</i>
<i> at night.</i>

08:27.841 --> 08:30.242
(soft growling)

08:33.780 --> 08:39.684
<i> And while no one ever saw</i>
<i> Sardu again,</i>

08:39.686 --> 08:43.555
<i> some said they heard</i>
<i> his cane in the night.</i>

08:43.557 --> 08:46.057
(tapping on window)

08:46.059 --> 08:48.860
(tapping knife on table)

08:56.470 --> 08:58.470
Evil...

08:58.472 --> 09:01.406
lurks in the world, Abraham,

09:01.408 --> 09:03.508
in many forms.

09:03.510 --> 09:07.345
Some familiar, some not.

09:07.347 --> 09:10.315
You must stop it.

09:10.317 --> 09:13.351
We all must.

09:13.353 --> 09:15.921
(cane tapping on floor)

09:23.430 --> 09:25.664
(tires screeching)
(siren blaring)

09:38.178 --> 09:40.912
(horrific screaming)

09:48.689 --> 09:50.855
(Master croaking)

09:50.857 --> 09:53.525
(Master screaming)
- In the name

09:53.527 --> 09:57.095
of all that is HOLY!

10:03.036 --> 10:06.304
(screaming)

