13:10.891 --> 13:13.057
(distant tires squealing)

13:17.264 --> 13:19.330
- Never thought
I'd be nostalgic

13:19.332 --> 13:21.800
for rats!
- Yeah!

13:21.802 --> 13:24.269
Vampire-proofing is, uh,

13:24.271 --> 13:26.237
a lot more labor intensive than

13:26.239 --> 13:28.840
rat-proofing.
- Where's Setrakian?

13:28.842 --> 13:31.976
- He left before I got up.
- Where to?

13:31.978 --> 13:34.012
- He's not big on leaving notes.

13:34.014 --> 13:36.014
Hey, you wanna
help me out with this?

13:39.486 --> 13:42.320
(distant sirens blaring)

13:42.322 --> 13:44.455
(fire truck horn honking)

13:44.457 --> 13:46.691
- He said sunlight
would kill that thing.

13:46.693 --> 13:49.694
We chased it into the sun,
it got away.

13:49.696 --> 13:51.696
- Everybody makes mistakes,

13:51.698 --> 13:54.132
even vampire hunters...

13:54.134 --> 13:56.134
even doctors.

13:56.136 --> 13:58.970
- So you're still on board?
You're still ready

13:58.972 --> 14:01.206
to follow him down
every dark tunnel in the city?

14:01.208 --> 14:03.007
- Yeah.

14:03.009 --> 14:05.610
But I've got my own plan.
- Which is?

14:05.612 --> 14:07.879
- I'm gonna secure my place,

14:07.881 --> 14:10.315
then next door,

14:10.317 --> 14:12.851
then the block,
and then the next block.

14:15.989 --> 14:18.289
- The ground game
isn't for me.

14:18.291 --> 14:22.160
(distant yelling)
- So what are you gonna do?

14:22.162 --> 14:24.128
(wind whistling)

14:24.130 --> 14:27.232
- Well, seeing as how as a
vampire hunter, I'm total shit,

14:27.234 --> 14:29.701
I'm gonna go back
to being a doctor.

14:36.409 --> 14:38.576
- (man):<i> At the press conference</i>
<i> in Rose Garden earlier today,</i>

14:38.578 --> 14:40.912
<i> the President announced...</i>
- (Eph): Nora?

14:40.914 --> 14:43.047
-<i> ...that he has ordered another</i>
<i> 2000 National Guard's troops</i>

14:43.049 --> 14:45.316
<i> to deploy in Manhattan...</i>
- Nora?

14:45.318 --> 14:47.352
-<i> ...secure government buildings</i>
<i> and crucial infrastructure.</i>

14:47.354 --> 14:49.354
- (Eph): You ready?
- (Nora): Yeah.

14:49.356 --> 14:52.023
-<i> This brings the total number</i>
<i> of National Guard troops</i>

14:52.025 --> 14:55.493
<i> in the city to 10,000.</i>
- Zack is still asleep.

14:55.495 --> 14:58.596
- Dutch. You could use
some ventilation there.

14:58.598 --> 15:00.565
- Yeah. And a latte
with almond milk

15:00.567 --> 15:02.400
and a massage
from the Four Seasons.

15:02.402 --> 15:04.502
- When Zack gets up,
could you make sure

15:04.504 --> 15:06.671
he gets some breakfast?
- (Dutch): Where are you going?

15:06.673 --> 15:08.673
- Out.
- Got it. Yeah, no problem.

15:08.675 --> 15:11.276
I'll just feed your kid and make
sure this place is vampire-safe

15:11.278 --> 15:12.744
for you.
- Is there a problem?

15:12.746 --> 15:14.245
- I just said
there wasn't a problem.

15:14.247 --> 15:16.014
- Sounds like there's a problem.

15:16.016 --> 15:18.349
- If there was a problem, I'd
tell you there was a problem.

15:18.351 --> 15:19.384
You're just so
bloody presumptuous.

15:19.386 --> 15:21.619
- Am I?
- God, yes!

15:21.621 --> 15:23.621
-<i> ...chairman of the Armed</i>
<i> Services Committee expressed</i>

15:23.623 --> 15:26.190
<i> concern at a hearing today...</i>
- Please and thank you.

15:26.192 --> 15:29.093
- Whatever, and you're welcome.

15:29.095 --> 15:31.629
-<i> ...with Russia's</i>
<i> surprise annexation</i>

15:31.631 --> 15:34.699
<i> of Latvia and Lithuania.</i>

15:37.137 --> 15:41.739
(wind blowing)

15:41.741 --> 15:44.676
(growling)

15:56.890 --> 15:59.223
- My Master...

15:59.225 --> 16:02.293
(translated from German)

16:51.778 --> 16:53.845
(Master groaning)

16:56.616 --> 16:59.450
(Master moaning)

17:13.166 --> 17:15.466
- I'm removing the bag now.

17:15.468 --> 17:17.468
Any sudden moves
and I'll kill you.

17:17.470 --> 17:21.572
Nod if you understand.

17:28.481 --> 17:30.481
- Wait!

17:30.483 --> 17:34.152
I know this guy.
- Give me my cane!

17:34.154 --> 17:36.020
- No way, old man.

17:39.993 --> 17:43.027
He owns a pawnshop
in my neighborhood in Harlem.

17:43.029 --> 17:45.930
He's not a threat.
- You're the idiot brother

17:45.932 --> 17:47.932
of the man-child who stole

17:47.934 --> 17:51.169
my clock!
- I brought you your clock back.

17:51.171 --> 17:53.171
- OK, shut up.
Come on, let's go!

17:53.173 --> 17:55.073
- That way.

18:05.218 --> 18:07.885
- You work for this filth?

18:07.887 --> 18:09.887
- You know what they say.
You've got to stay

18:09.889 --> 18:12.123
on top of the food chain, O.G.

18:12.125 --> 18:15.393
- You and five<i> strigoi?</i>

18:15.395 --> 18:18.029
Not very smart.
- Silence.

18:18.031 --> 18:21.766
You will approach
with all due respect.

18:31.978 --> 18:34.112
(growling and croaking)

18:56.769 --> 18:58.769
- They exist...

18:58.771 --> 19:01.806
the Ancients.

19:04.077 --> 19:06.911
- They're sleeping now,

19:06.913 --> 19:10.515
but they can hear
and understand everything.

19:10.517 --> 19:14.018
I speak for them.

19:14.020 --> 19:16.020
What do you know

19:16.022 --> 19:19.023
of the seventh one
of their kind?

19:19.025 --> 19:21.926
- The... the seventh?

19:21.928 --> 19:25.530
- The one you call the Master.
You injured him.

19:25.532 --> 19:27.832
- How do you know this?

19:27.834 --> 19:30.868
- The seven share
a common mind.

19:30.870 --> 19:33.638
But the seventh...

19:33.640 --> 19:36.541
has the power
to disrupt thought.

19:36.543 --> 19:40.378
When you injured him,
he lost control,

19:40.380 --> 19:43.147
so they saw you fighting.

19:43.149 --> 19:46.150
- And now, he has
recovered enough

19:46.152 --> 19:48.152
to shield himself from you

19:48.154 --> 19:50.188
once again.

19:52.392 --> 19:55.026
What do you want?

19:57.897 --> 20:00.464
- They want to make
an alliance with you.

20:00.466 --> 20:04.802
Sometimes great enemies
become allies,

20:04.804 --> 20:06.737
so they can fight
a common foe.

20:06.739 --> 20:08.673
- Do they know how

20:08.675 --> 20:11.075
to kill him?

20:11.077 --> 20:13.211
- I think, for obvious reasons,

20:13.213 --> 20:15.346
they won't answer that question.

20:15.348 --> 20:18.482
- Then I don't see
how they can help me.

20:18.484 --> 20:20.751
- No.

20:20.753 --> 20:23.187
You're here to help them.

20:23.189 --> 20:25.189
Over the millennia,
they have gathered

20:25.191 --> 20:27.658
vast resources that could
help you in your hunt.

20:27.660 --> 20:30.761
- A legend has passed down

20:30.763 --> 20:33.364
through the centuries...

20:33.366 --> 20:36.267
concerning a book,

20:36.269 --> 20:39.070
an ancient tome

20:39.072 --> 20:41.706
of uncertain provenance

20:41.708 --> 20:44.275
and some say divine inspiration:

20:44.277 --> 20:47.345
the<i> Occido Lumen.</i>

20:47.347 --> 20:50.281
(Ancients growling)

20:51.918 --> 20:54.051
- And, uh...

20:54.053 --> 20:56.787
what do you know
of this book?

20:56.789 --> 20:59.724
- I now have proof
that it exists.

20:59.726 --> 21:02.260
(weird bark)

21:05.365 --> 21:07.732
What are they saying?

21:07.734 --> 21:11.135
- They're trying to decide
whether you should live.

21:11.137 --> 21:13.971
- I vowed to hunt the Master

21:13.973 --> 21:16.374
until the day I die.

21:16.376 --> 21:20.211
If today is that day, so be it!

21:20.213 --> 21:22.280
(Ancient growling)

21:22.282 --> 21:25.316
- All right.

21:25.318 --> 21:27.752
Here's the bargain.

21:27.754 --> 21:29.754
They'll let you live,

21:29.756 --> 21:32.223
but you must guarantee

21:32.225 --> 21:34.625
that when you find the Master,
you will alert us.

21:37.497 --> 21:39.497
- Fair enough.

21:39.499 --> 21:41.399
(Ancient growling)

21:41.401 --> 21:43.067
- Oh?

21:43.069 --> 21:47.004
They're waking now, yeah.

21:47.006 --> 21:49.073
We'd best leave.

21:49.075 --> 21:51.742
They're gonna be hungry.

21:51.744 --> 21:54.178
(man grunting)

21:57.750 --> 22:01.152
No! Please!

22:08.995 --> 22:12.763
(naked man grunting and panting)

22:12.765 --> 22:15.533
(Ancient grumbling)

22:15.535 --> 22:17.601
(chain rattling)

22:17.603 --> 22:19.337
Ah!

22:25.545 --> 22:28.612
(naked man screaming)

22:47.133 --> 22:50.868
(naked man screaming)

22:55.641 --> 22:58.309
- As you walk on
in the daylight...

23:00.880 --> 23:03.314
...never forget this.

23:03.316 --> 23:05.716
(Ancients grunting)

23:19.198 --> 23:20.965
